<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,685,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,685,710]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The monobasic 
<taxonomicName box="[468,623,685,710]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[468,623,685,710]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Argyrophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as defined here is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[1074,1216,686,709]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Punargentus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1074,1216,686,709]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Punargentus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most notably by a singly pupillated M 
<number box="[383,392,722,746]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
-M 
<number box="[429,442,722,746]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
VFW ocellus, valvae that are are rounder and wider at the distal end than those in 
<emphasis box="[151,300,758,781]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName box="[151,296,758,781]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Punargentus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Punargentus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
a narrower saccus, and aedeagus with medial wings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,685,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,793,818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pyrcz" box="[329,644,793,818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Pyrcz, T. W. &amp; Wojtusiak, J. (2010) A new species of Argyrophorus Blanchard from northern Peru and considerations on the value of wing venation as a source of synapomorphies in some temperate Neotropical Satyrinae (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae). Genus, 21, 605 - 613." type="journal article" year="2010">
Pyrcz &amp; Wojtusiak (
<number box="[577,636,794,818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
redefined 
<taxonomicName box="[778,933,793,818]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[778,933,793,818]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Argyrophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using head morphology, wing patterning, venation, wing shape, and male genitalic characters, apparently to be inclusive of 
<taxonomicName box="[1161,1304,829,854]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Etcheverrius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1161,1304,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etcheverrius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1326,1429,829,854]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Palmaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1326,1429,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Palmaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,311,866,889]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pampasatyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,311,866,889]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pampasatyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[370,512,866,889]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Punargentus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[370,512,866,889]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Punargentus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(although they neglected to provide a list of which species are included in their circumscription of the genus, and were not clear as to whether 
<taxonomicName box="[886,1118,902,925]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pamperis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poaoeneis">
<emphasis box="[886,1118,902,925]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pamperis poaoeneis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is or is not included). This situation was clarified somewhat by 
<bibRefCitation box="[573,821,937,962]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Cerdena, J. A., Pyrcz, T. W. &amp; Zacca, T. (2014) High Andean butterflies from southern Peru, I. Dry puna Satyrinae, with the description of two new taxa and three new records from Peru (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae). Revista Peruana de Biologia, 21, 213 - 222." type="journal article">
Cerdeña 
<emphasis box="[676,726,937,962]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[752,813,938,962]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who reported that Pyrcz (
<number box="[1128,1187,938,962]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2010.0">2010</number>
) synonymized “nine” genera under 
<taxonomicName box="[312,467,973,998]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[312,467,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Argyrophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(they listed seven: 
<taxonomicName box="[704,847,973,998]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Etcheverrius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[704,847,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etcheverrius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[866,1003,973,998]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Neomaniola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[866,1003,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Neomaniola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1021,1123,973,998]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Palmaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1021,1123,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Palmaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1143,1303,974,997]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pampasatyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1143,1303,974,997]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pampasatyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1322,1429,974,997]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pamperis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1322,1429,974,997]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pamperis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,293,1010,1033]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Punargentus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,293,1010,1033]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Punargentus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[347,514,1009,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Stuardosatyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[347,514,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Stuardosatyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pyrcz" box="[701,846,1010,1034]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Pyrcz, T. W. (2012) A new species of satyrine butterfly from Patagonia in more than a century and revisional notes on the genus Faunula C. Felder &amp; R. Felder (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae: Satyrinae). Zootaxa, 3342, 60 - 68." type="journal article" year="2012">
Pyrcz (
<number box="[779,838,1010,1034]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
moved 
<taxonomicName box="[936,1184,1009,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Neomaniola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euripides">
<emphasis box="[936,1184,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Neomaniola euripides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[1252,1407,1009,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1252,1407,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Argyrophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[151,246,1045,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Faunula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,246,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Faunula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[260,499,1045,1070]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Cerdena, J. A., Pyrcz, T. W. &amp; Zacca, T. (2014) High Andean butterflies from southern Peru, I. Dry puna Satyrinae, with the description of two new taxa and three new records from Peru (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae). Revista Peruana de Biologia, 21, 213 - 222." type="journal article">
Cerdeña 
<emphasis box="[361,410,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[432,491,1046,1070]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
also noted that 
<taxonomicName box="[677,837,1046,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pampasatyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[677,837,1046,1069]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pampasatyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely-related to, but distinct from 
<emphasis box="[1274,1437,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName box="[1274,1433,1045,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Argyrophorus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
They reported the latter to contain 
<number box="[554,581,1082,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="11.0">11</number>
species—presumably the species previously included by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamas" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Lamas, G. &amp; Viloria, A. (2004) Subtribes Erebiina and Hypocystina. In: Lamas, G. (Ed) Checklist: Part 4 A. Hesperioidea- Papilionoidea. In: Heppner, J. B. (Ed.), Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Association for Tropical Lepidoptera, Inc. / Scientific Publishers, Gainesville, FL, pp. 215 - 217." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Lamas &amp; Viloria (
<number box="[159,218,1118,1142]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[265,420,1117,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[265,420,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Argyrophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[440,452,1118,1142]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[486,500,1118,1142]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
subsequently described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pyrcz" box="[818,1111,1117,1142]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Pyrcz, T. W. &amp; Wojtusiak, J. (2010) A new species of Argyrophorus Blanchard from northern Peru and considerations on the value of wing venation as a source of synapomorphies in some temperate Neotropical Satyrinae (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae). Genus, 21, 605 - 613." type="journal article" year="2010">
Pyrcz &amp; Wojtusiak, 
<number box="[1051,1111,1118,1142]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[1132,1275,1117,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Etcheverrius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1132,1275,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etcheverrius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[1294,1310,1118,1142]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[1333,1436,1117,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Palmaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1333,1436,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Palmaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[160,176,1154,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[198,306,1154,1177]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pamperis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[198,306,1154,1177]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pamperis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[324,336,1154,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[403,545,1154,1177]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Punargentus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[403,545,1154,1177]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Punargentus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[562,579,1154,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
). According to our cladogram (
<figureCitation box="[936,1002,1153,1178]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="78.[151,250,1782,1804]" captionTargetBox="[187,1390,212,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@78.[180,1408,195,1758]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 1. One of six equally parsimonious trees for Neosatyriti and selected pronophiline outgroups, based on 4071 bp of concatenated DNA sequence from mtDNA COI-COII, elongation factor 1 - alpha and wingless. Length = 8955 steps, CIx = 0.2435; RI = 0.4729." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271705/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[989,1002,1154,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), that circumscription is polyphyletic: 
<taxonomicName box="[151,306,1189,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,306,1189,1214]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Argyrophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[363,470,1190,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pamperis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[363,470,1190,1213]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pamperis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are phylogenetically distinct from 
<taxonomicName box="[870,1012,1190,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Punargentus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[870,1012,1190,1213]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Punargentus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(here circumscribed more broadly to include 
<taxonomicName box="[240,383,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Etcheverrius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[240,383,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etcheverrius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[436,539,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Palmaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[436,539,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Palmaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and its sister genus, 
<taxonomicName box="[779,939,1226,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pampasatyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[779,939,1226,1249]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pampasatyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pyrcz" box="[953,1246,1225,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Pyrcz, T. W. &amp; Wojtusiak, J. (2010) A new species of Argyrophorus Blanchard from northern Peru and considerations on the value of wing venation as a source of synapomorphies in some temperate Neotropical Satyrinae (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae). Genus, 21, 605 - 613." type="journal article" year="2010">
Pyrcz &amp; Wojtusiak (
<number box="[1178,1237,1226,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
placed their new species 
<taxonomicName box="[240,361,1261,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Punargentus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blanchardi">
<emphasis box="[240,361,1261,1286]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">blanchardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[400,555,1261,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[400,555,1261,1286]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Argyrophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using their broader definition, but the similarities in the VFW M 
<number box="[1300,1309,1262,1286]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
-M 
<number box="[1346,1359,1262,1286]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
ocelli, and the lack of medial appendages on the aedeagus suggest that it belongs in 
<emphasis box="[1015,1164,1298,1321]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName box="[1015,1160,1298,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Punargentus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Punargentus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
instead.
</paragraph>
